Fetch 4.0.2 ReadMeFetch is a Macintosh program for transferring files using the File Transfer Protocol (FTP) on a TCP/IP network, such as the Internet. This allows a networked Macintosh to exchange files with any FTP server on the same network. Fetch runs on Mac OS System 7.0 or newer, including Mac OS X.  Fetch can be used to:¥ Put web pages onto a web server.¥ Rename, move, delete, and change the permissions of files on a web server in order to maintain a web site.¥ Transfer documents to an FTP site run by a printer or service bureau.¥ Put image files on a web server in order to reference them in eBay auction listings.¥ Move files between your Macintosh and Macintosh, UNIX, Windows, NetWare or other sorts of computers, as well as specialized equipment including medical imaging machines, image editing systems and photo processing equipment.If you have questions or comments about Fetch, please visit the message board at http://fetchsoftworks.com.This copy of Fetch is version 4.0.2, released April, 2002.Fetch is Copyright © 2000, Trustees of Dartmouth College, © 2002, Fetch Softworks.  This copy of Fetch is sold under license by Fetch Softworks.This trial copy of Fetch will work for 15 days before requiring a serial number, which can be obtained by choosing "Purchase..." from the Apple menu.  A single-user license is $25 US.  Users closely affiliated with educational or non-profit charitable organizations (government research laboratories excepted) may apply for a free license at http://fetchsoftworks.com.  Multi-user licenses are also available.Contact Information:Fetch Softworks P.O. Box 5612 Hanover, NH 03755USAhttp://fetchsoftworks.comEmail: info@fetchsoftworks.com Voicemail/Fax: +1 (603) 619-0387 or (866) 422-0023